#: ../../../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.13/site-packages/numpy/random/__init__.py:docstring
#: of numpy.random.default_rng:8
msgid ""
"A seed to initialize the `BitGenerator`. If None, then fresh, unpredictable "
"entropy will be pulled from the OS. If an ``int`` or ``array_like[ints]`` is "
"passed, then all values must be non-negative and will be passed to "
"`SeedSequence` to derive the initial `BitGenerator` state. One may also pass "
"in a `SeedSequence` instance. Additionally, when passed a `BitGenerator`, it "
"will be wrapped by `Generator`. If passed a `Generator`, it will be returned "
"unaltered. When passed a legacy `RandomState` instance it will be coerced to "
"a `Generator`."
msgstr ""

